commit.message:
default: fix a dark spot

- minor dark spot on the bubble is distracting

Update README.md for 39.0.3

Signed-off-by: Adam Williamson <awilliam@redhat.com>

default: avoid moire with bayer

- the bayer dithering method is very pleasing to the eye, but at certain resolutions and scale filtering can result in moire patterns.
- the update uses an 'arithmetic add' method that is aesthetically somewhere between the ordered bayer and randomness of floyd steinberg

Fix whitespace in default/Makefile

Makefile whitespace is a goddamn mystery.

Signed-off-by: Adam Williamson <awilliam@redhat.com>

There's no 'optimization' now, so drop that bit of the comment

Signed-off-by: Adam Williamson <awilliam@redhat.com>

default, extras: remove auto-optimalization

- Right now pngquant will produce 8bit fixed color palette PNGs,
  which is absolutely not what you want in 95% of cases. No amount
  of dithering will result in no color banding when the abstract
  wallpaper is relying on 24 or even 48bit.
- Avoiding color banding with dithering is a deliberate controlled
  process done during the creation

Fixes https://github.com/fedoradesign/backgrounds/issues/57

default: 8bit color & dither

- avoid color banding by bayer dithering and using 8bit rather than 16bit depth
  of the original.

Bump from 37 to 39 in Attribution-Extras

Signed-off-by: Adam Williamson <awilliam@redhat.com>

Drop another comment that seems to be dangerous

It seems like one attempt to build the package for Rawhide
failed around here, and I don't think "commenting out" lines in
for loops in Makefiles like this is ever a safe idea, so let's
take it out.

Signed-off-by: Adam Williamson <awilliam@redhat.com>

Bump versions for 39.0.1

Signed-off-by: Adam Williamson <awilliam@redhat.com>

Add the missing budgie XML config file

This has been in the .tar.xz tarballs Luya has uploaded since
the Budgie support was added, but it is not actually in the git
repo. I think he has it in his local checkout but forgot to git
add it, and he's been producing the tarballs from his local
checkout without using `git archive`, so the file wound up in
there despite not being in source control.

Signed-off-by: Adam Williamson <awilliam@redhat.com>

Move a comment in extras/Makefile which breaks the build

You can't put a comment in the middle of a for loop like this.

Signed-off-by: Adam Williamson <awilliam@redhat.com>
